n imprisoned in Seagate Prison's supervillain cell block.{{issue|date=March 2013}}\n\n===Civil War===\nDuring the ''[[Civil War (comics)|Civil War]]'' event, he was captured by [[Baron Zemo]]'s [[Thunderbolts (comics)|Thunderbolts]] and forced to join them or face jail time.{{Issue|date=April 2009}} With the Thunderbolts army, he went on a mission to Sydney, Australia.{{issue|date=March 2013}}\n\n==Powers and abilities==\nSnake Marston has no super human powers; he is however a master contortionist who can hold an opponent helpless by winding himself around them.\n\n==In other media==\n===Video games===\n* Snake Marston is mentioned in ''[[Spider-Man: Shattered Dimensions]]''. [[Hammerhead (comics)|Hammerhead]]'s henchmen mentioned how Marston uses his contortionist abilities to attempt to seduce [[Frederick Foswell|Janice Foswell]], something her boyfriend Hammerhead is unhappy about.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Marvunapp|http://www.marvunapp.com/Appendix4/marstonsnake.htm|Snake Marston}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Marston, Snake}}\n[[Category:Comics characters introduced in 1980]]\n[[Category:Characters created by Steve Ditko]]\n[[Category:Marvel Comics supervillains]]\n[[Category:Fictional contortionists]]\n\n{{Marvel-villain-stub}}"}]}}}}